MISHKO raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and tired in the lane.

BOAT SONG pressed the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, dropped back to chase the leader from the two path coming around the turn and kept on to the wire. ASTRONAUT OSCAR chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the three path and chased the winner home in the lane. WARRIOR BOSS tracked the pace setters on the inside early, saved ground around the bend and finished evenly. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 7 7 1/2F Turf CR: 73. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR MINNESOTA BRED WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Minnesota Bred Claiming Price $15,000. (If management d eems it inadvisable to run this race on the turf, two-year-old races will be run at 6 and 1/2 furlongs and races for three-year-olds and up will be run at a distance of 1 mile on the main track.) (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELEGANCE N TONIC raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, angled in to save ground around the far bend, began a bid passing the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. SHEZONEZESTREET raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, raced in the four path around the second bend, swung wide into the lane and gained ground late. JEWEL AZUL raced in the four path early, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far bend from the three path and improved position in the stretch. GIVE EM SHADE raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and chased the winner home from there. CHAPARRITA raced in the two path early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path and was outkicked in the lane while finishing evenly. BARBARA ROHLOFF led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the far bend and weakened in the lane. CHOCOLATE FRECKLES stayed in the gate when the doors opened, trailed the field from the three path through the opening half mile, swung out to the five path for the run around the second turn and was not a threat. DURA THE EXPLORER raced in the three path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and faded from there. MAY DISCO raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and was empty in the stretch. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE START. UPON REVIEW, IT WAS DETERMINED THAT HORSE EIGHT, CHOCOLATE FRECKLES, HAD A FAIR BEGINNNING AND NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.
